<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key C, modal ending on E7 (Phrygian dominant). Dramatic chromatic harmony.
- E major (III chord): E2-B2-E3-G#3 throughout. Non-diatonic G# always marked accid="s".
- LH: Am A2-E3-A3-C4; G G2-D3-G3-B3; C C2-G2-C3-E3; F F2-C3-F3-A3.
- RH: Mostly 2-note thirds, E5/G#4 on E major chords.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- G# always descending into Am chord tone (G# → A)
- Bar 17: F-Gm chromatic motion before final E
- Contrary motion bars 1-2: melody descends B-E-B, bass rises E-Am-G

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opening: Dramatic E major opening, modal color
- Bars 1-10: Two strophes with E-Am oscillation
- Bars 11-17: Through-composed middle
- Bar 18: Final E7 Phrygian close
-->
